SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 87
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Eddie Smith to the
Public Charter School Commission.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-13-105, provides for the creation of
the Public Charter School Commission; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-13-105(b)(1)(A), provides that the
commission be composed of nine members appointed by the governor; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-13-105(c)(3), provides that at least
three members from each grand division of the state must serve on the commission; and
WHEREAS, Governor Bill Lee, acting pursuant to Tennessee Code Annotated, Section
49-13-105, has appointed Eddie Smith as a member of the Public Charter School Commission
representing East Tennessee for a term that will expire on June 30, 2029; and
WHEREAS, former State Representative Eddie Smith is the current director of programs
and development for Childhelp Tennessee, a child abuse and neglect organization in Knoxville;
and
WHEREAS, he earned a Bachelor of Science degree from Tusculum College; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-13-105(b)(1)(A), provides that
each appointed member shall be confirmed by joint resolution of the General Assembly; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby confirm the appointment of Eddie Smith
to the Public Charter School Commission for a term that will expire on June 30, 2029.
